<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: MAD-1, MAD-2, MAD-R differences?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9479&amp;p=131339#p131339"><![CDATA[
You have to forgive me for those mistake, I was rushing to do this while doing something else. Because of my lack of focus, I think must have looked at the 36 pin maskrom pinout once or twice instead of the 32 pin one while checking pin-out on Caitsith's website. That explain the mix-up with pin 1, 17 and 18. I was also not looking at the right pinout for the SRAM and was using the 256kbit ram pinout instead of the 6265 for some reason. I rechecked the PCB and here's the corrected pin out:<br /><br />01 /CS (ROM U2)<br />02 SRAM /CS<br />03 DSP1B /CS<br />04 DSP1B /RESET<br />05 SRAM Vcc<br />06 Vcc<br />07 Vbat<br />08 GND<br />09 /OSC Input<br />10 DSP1B /Clock<br />11 <s>SRAM /CS2</s> /Reset<br />12 Vcc<br />13 /CART (Pad 49)<br />14 BA6 (Pad 47)<br />15 BA4 (Pad 49)<br />16 A14 (Pad 39)<br />17 A13 (Pad 38)<br />18 /CS (ROM U1)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4859">SkinnyV</a> — Sat Jul 19, 2014 8:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
